Aim

To implement One-Hot Encoding for words or characters to convert textual data into numerical form suitable for machine learning models.

Description

Machine learning algorithms cannot directly process text data.
One-Hot Encoding is a technique that converts each unique word or character into a binary vector where:
•	Only one position is 1
•	All other positions are 0
This representation helps models understand categorical text data.

Program:
sentence = "I love AI"
words = sentence.split()
unique_words = list(set(words))
one_hot = {}
for word in unique_words:
    vector = []
    for w in unique_words:
        if word == w:
            vector.append(1)
        else:
            vector.append(0)
    one_hot[word] = vector
for word, vector in one_hot.items():
    print(word, ":", vector)# Step 1: Input sentence
